Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light-brown pottery vessel, exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip, now very worn, and very faint traces of one line of black-painted hieratic text identifying the contents.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393179) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393179)
